description: The anti-occupation NGO Combatants for Peace works to organize joint actions between young people living in the West Bank and in Israel. The group faces the challenge of rebuilding trust between both sides, torn apart by two years of war in Gaza.

headline: Louvre heist: All suspected members of the commando group now charged
description: A man suspected of being the fourth and final accomplice in the team that stole jewels from the Louvre in broad daylight has been placed in provisional detention. He was already known to authorities.

headline: The housing crisis is fueling the far-right vote
description: In France, a growing share of the population is struggling to find housing. The shortage, which especially affects the working and middle classes, is generating resentment with consequences at the ballot box.

headline: Germany pushes ahead to become Europe's leading space power
description: Member states of the European Space Agency, meeting in Bremen, approved a €22.1 billion budget for 2026-2028 – a 32% increase. Germany will contribute €5.1 billion, or 23% of the funds, taking on a leadership role in Europe's space program.

headline: Forgotten Louvre security report highlighted specific balcony used by crown jewel thieves
description: Le Monde has learned that a 2018 security audit explicitly identified the balcony used by the thieves as a point of vulnerability, even noting the possibility that a freight lift could be used to access it.
